v/31-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(36,1,'2012-04-19 20:48:11','2012-04-19 20:48:11','DANCE EXPLORATION\r\nOur Dance Exploration classes provide beginning dancers an introduction to tap, jazz and ballet technique. The dancers will work on rhythm, balance, and coordination in fun and exciting atmosphere! These classes perform twice in our annual end of year recital. Dance Ex 1: Beginning 2-3 years old Dance Ex 2: 3-4 year olds Dance Ex 3: 4-5 year olds\r\n\r\nBASIC TAP, JAZZ &amp; BALLET\r\nBasic classes continue to build on the fundamentals of each of these styles. Bridging the gap from the dance exploration classes to the level 1 classes.\r\n\r\nBALLET\r\nBallet is the foundation for all styles of dance. Students will develop flexibility, strength, control, coordination, line and musicality. Ballet Level 2 and above are required to take a minimum of two ballet classes per week. We suggest that every student at Steps Dance Center enroll in at least one ballet class.\r\n\r\nPOINTE\r\nFor those students who want to take their ballet training to the next level. Students must be recommended for pointe by their ballet instructor. Students must be enrolled in at least one additional ballet class per week.\r\n\r\nJAZZ\r\nStudents will learn ballet based technique (turns, leaps, jumps) while learning to put them together in exciting, energetic combinations. Students will get to experience traditional jazz (Broadway, Fosse, Giordano) to Contemporary style jazz. TAP\r\nOur tap classes focus on all the different styles of tap. Students can experience a range from the always entertaining Broadway style to the modern day style of hoofing. No matter what style they experience the art of producing rhythm with your feet is a great style to add to any dance repertoire!\r\n\r\nHIP HOP\r\nSteps hip hop classes explore multiple styles of the culture and all the current moves! Students will study both new school (jazz funk, krump, etc. ) to old school (popping, locking, breaking, whacking, voguing , etc… ) These classes will be sure to get you groovin’ with all the latest moves!\r\n\r\nLYRICAL\r\nOur lyrical classes fuse the technique and style of both ballet and jazz. Students work on expressing emotion while telling a story through the use of the lyrics and music. This is a great style for any dancer with training in ballet or jazz who want to expand their knowledge in different styles. Pre-requisite: Student must also be registered in the same level ballet or jazz class.\r\n\r\nPOM TECHNIQUE\r\nPreparing for an audition or just want to brush up on your technical skills? Our pom technique class will get you conditioned and trained for any junior high, high school or college dance team. This class focuses on flexibility, pom motions, turns, jumps, leaps and tricks. This class is intended for middle school and high school aged students. PILATES\r\nThis Pilates class will consist of basic mat exercises with a focus on strengthening the core muscles of the body as well as improving whole-body coordination, flexibility and control. Students will progress at their own rate, and modifications will be made to accommodate injuries or other physical limitations. An exercise mat will be required for participation in this class.\r\n\r\nTURNS &amp; TECHNIQUE\r\nThis is a jazz based class that focuses on the technical elements of jazz dancing. The emphasis will be on fine tuning technical elements such as pirouette turns, leaps and jumps, while also working on strength and conditioning.\r\n\r\nPlacement into our classes is based upon level of experience. Please use the guide below to determine your placement. If you have any questions, a member of our desk staff will be able to help you at 630-499-5678.\r\n\r\nLevel 1 Beginning level; Level 2 Beginning intermediate; pre-requisite: 2 years in level 1 Level 3 Intermediate: Pre-requisite 2 years in level 2 Level 4 Intermediate / advanced: pre-requisite: 2years in level 3 Level 5 Advanced pre-requisite: 2 years in level 4','Schedule','','inherit','open','open','','21-revision-2','','','2012-04-19 20:48:11','2012-04-19 20:48:11','',21,'http://steps.dev/21-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(37,1,'2012-04-19 20:49:05','2012-04-19 20:49:05','As dance is a performance art, Steps Dance Center strongly believes in our students gaining confidence in dance through performance on stage. Our dance year culminates in our year-end recital.\r\n\r\nOur recital is held at Neuqua Valley High School, located at 2360 95th Street Naperville, IL 60564.\r\n\r\nOur 2012 Recital will be held on June 8, 9, and 10. A mandatory dress rehearsal will be held on June 5, 6, and 7.','Recital','','inherit','open','open','','25-revision-2','','','2012-04-19 20:49:05','2012-04-19 20:49:05','',25,'http://steps.dev/25-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(38,1,'2012-04-19 20:48:43','2012-04-19 20:48:43','Classes Start Tue, Sept 6th -thru- Sat, June 2nd\r\n\r\nLength of Class Quarterly Payment\r\n45 Minutes $115 60 Minutes $130 75 Minutes $160 90 Minutes $185 REGISTRATION FEE Annual Fee - $35 per student\r\n\r\nFAMILY DISCOUNTS We offer a 5% discount to families enrolled in three or more classes. 6 or more classes, 10% discount.\r\n\r\nPAYMENT PLAN Four equal payments will be due as follows: 1st -- At Registration (Registration begins August 13th &amp; 14th 10am-3pm ) 2nd -- Saturday, October 29, 2011 3rd -- Saturday, Jan 22, 2012 4th -- Saturday, March 26, 2012\r\n\r\nCOSTUME FEES Due November 12, 2011\r\n\r\n*You may choose Auto Pay or pay by check/cash. All families must have a valid credit card on file.\r\n\r\n*All fees are non refundable. However, make up classes are available.\r\n\r\nPlease note: There is a $35 Return Check fee','Rates','','inherit','open','open','','23-revision-2','','','2012-04-19 20:48:43','2012-04-19 20:48:43','',23,'http://steps.dev/23-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(40,1,'2012-04-19 20:49:34','2012-04-19 20:49:34','Bringing the Best of Chicago Dance to the Suburbs\r\n\r\nOur Steps Dance